</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucaillougna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 559<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 11:35:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1488.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just a question</span><hr size=1> If you know the person is irritated with their current group because of excessive deaths, boring location, or other things, sending tells with an offer of something different would be acceptable, but accept a refusal.<br>
<br>
Walking up to a group and saying to one member (even if it is only a 2 man group) that you'd like them in your group is horrible horrible bad form and entirely rude.  Think about the others in that group.  You are effectively telling them they suck.  You are telling them the person you are asking shouldn't waste his/her time with them.<br>
<br>
If the person in the group you want to ask is needed for a certain skill he/she possesses, appologise to the group and ask them if it would be alright to &quot;steal&quot; or borrow the person for this specific task.  Again... make sure you keep in mind the rest of the group members, not just the one you are asking.  <br>
<br>
I also agree with being forthright to your potential group when you join if you have a limited time or are waiting for an opening in another place -before- you hit the accept button.<br>
<br>
A group is made up of individuals, keep in mind they have feelings, too.<br>
<br>
-Caillou Kyrielle<br>
Bippin's betrothed<br>
